  <static seed="163" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring470.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{36x^{4}-121}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(6x^{2}+11\right)\mathopen{}\left(6x^{2}-11\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Note that the given expression is the <em>difference of squares</em></p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {36x^{4}-121} \amp  = ({6x}^2)^2-11^2\\
                            \amp  = {\left(6x^{2}+11\right)\mathopen{}\left(6x^{2}-11\right)}
            \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
